				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting in PoV &amp; PoS<a name="17680"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 5:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes it is definitely possible.  At 55 I kited: a tree frog (red), a planarian larva (red), a gamite frog (red) and a suit of rusty armor (blue) in POV.  ALL of the red stuff gave me exactly 2% regular xp but took about 8-9 minutes to kite (they resisted like h*ll).  The suit took a minute to kite and didnt give a visible xp budge (he's DC bait).   The larvae don't assist frogs and vice versa, but they do assist other larvae. I got hit once or twice for about 600 damage<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />A stun is almost guaranteed death.  
<br />

<br />
In POS I kited a hurricane nopthan at the zone in.  There's only one I could pull solo at 55, the travelers kept resisting lull.  That took way longer - probably 14 minutes and also gave 2% xp - maybe there's some sort of cap?
<br />

<br />
In conclusion, not worth it until higher levels and better chants- I get better xp swarming or even grouping. Nice to say you did it though<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
I'm sure golems, crawlers and arachnae in the wastelands could also be kited, but probably take even longer.</span></td>
