				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting in PoV &amp; PoS<a name="17811"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 29 04 1:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I just went to PoV the other night, and have a couple observations:
<br />

<br />
1.  There's a lot of stuff that's immune to snare.  This is good for bards, as most of the other soloing classes require snareable mobs to survive.
<br />

<br />
2.  Autofollow is REALLY laggy in this zone, and the followers tend to do those giant circles that aggro everything in range.
<br />

<br />
3.  The mobs here hit really hard.  Don't get too close, esp. at 55, as you will be dead VERY fast.  
<br />

<br />
At 55 I'd suggest twisting in Occlusion of Sound, esp. on the reds, it'll make your dots hit a lot better, even though you'll take a hit from only twisting 3.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
