			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting in PoV &amp; PoS<a name="18936"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 4 04 1:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There is an exclent place for chant kiting in PoV, very close to the zone and very low risk from the point of view of other players ending up as speed bumps.  
<br />

<br />
From zone in, check out the building right by the graveyard.  There's two guards inside that don't help you and very large round room.
<br />

<br />
This room is so perfect for Chant Kiting I'd almost think it was put there just for bards.  I did a lot of soloing in this room for both lvls and AA from 62-64.  Once you ding 65 the AA gain is halved so head to HoH or PoFire.
<br />

<br />
You can easily pull a nice pack of skellies simply with soft agro.  Larvaes and frogs also make nice victims.  Watch out for some of the named skellies that'll pop on you because they will summon.
<br />

<br />
Now the problem with waltzing 12 skellies around the room is that when you turn to get your new target, you can get 1-rounded if you don't have a fast system.  Best way I found to get my new target was to use Khazumi's with no target up and then let the pack hit me, therebye giving me a new target.  You'll also want to use kahzumi's on initial pull because sometimes the mobs won't follow you right into the building, but will warp on you instead.  Nothing like having 6 skellies warp on you to send you instantly to your bind point.
<br />

<br />
I made good cash off this camp, got lots of parchments which was nice because when I was doing this there weren't 30 copies of every song available in the baz, and also managed to make most of the AD key.  Once in a while you'll even get a train from somewhere agro on you and that's just a bonus.  The train will kind of warp into the room and join your pack, sometimes including the named crawler or spider, neither of which summon.
<br />

<br />
If you are extremely lucky, you might even get an instrument from this camp.  One of the non-summoning undead nameds drops a primary-equipable horn with a 2.8 mod on it.
<br />

<br />
One note of caution:  Don't try to pull the two guards at the entrance to the building.  They'll destroy you.
<br />

<br />
Dlandridel Cadance
<br />
Maestro of Grey Hawke
<br />
Karana Server</span></td>
