				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting in PoV &amp; PoS<a name="20624"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 11 04 12:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been exping in PoV and have used that room.  The biggest problem is getting the mobs in there without dying due to warping.  I think I've figured out a pretty good way to keep them from warping though... when you go up the stairs into the building, keep going straight until you're near the wall, then wait for the mobs to climb the stairs.  Important note is to not go back towards the stairs because they seem to warp on your if you do that... well I've died both times I did it.  
<br />

<br />
Another problem that happens infrequently is that the skellies seem to get stuck on each other and therefore stop chasing you in mid kite... this is bad because if you're doing a tight circle (along the first step up from middle), then you'll run around into melee range and get a quick trip to bind point.  This is avoidable, but this means you should be kiting in 3rd person view so that you can see them stop and you can simply discontinue your turning and avoid circling back into them.
<br />

<br />
Also, don't forget to loot the larvae's heart and skelly crystal thing, both are needed for HoH key... but exp is so fast I fully anticipate being 62 before having all the hearts and crystals.  And that's another reason why one might not want to pull too many mobs, rot time is at 27 or 28 minutes, so for me that means I don't want to pull more than 5 mobs.
<br />

<br />
Overall, I like using the room when I don't die getting the mobs in there.  =)  Another good place that I like to solo kite is behind the building where the wall slants towards the zone wall.  I still want to find a better spot to kite though, preferable an area not so close to trees, fairly flat, out of train paths, and near skellies.</span></td>
